{
  "text": "Oligonucleotides of 24 and 26 residues (sequences shown in Table 1 [CITATION_1] ) and recovered by the crush-soak method, precipitated with ethanol, resuspended and dialyzed against buffer consisting of 10 mM Tris, 0.1 mM EDTA, pH 8.0 at 20 \u00b1 1 C. DNA duplexes were prepared by annealing purified 5 0 -labeled oligonucleotides with slight excess of the complementary unlabeled strands. Single-stranded DNA (ssDNA) concentrations were measured spectrophotometrically using extinction coefficients provided by the manufacturer.",
